The article announces that President Obama has called for a group of experts to review intelligence and communications technologies. The group includes Richard Clarke, Michael Morell, Geoffrey Stone, Cass Sunstein, and Peter Swire, who have experience in national security, intelligence, oversight, privacy, and civil liberties. The purpose of the review is to advise the President on how the United States can use its technical collection capabilities to protect national security and advance foreign policy while respecting privacy and civil liberties. The President thanked the group members and expects to hear from them as their work progresses. The group will present their interim findings to the President within 60 days and provide a final report and recommendations.